## Estrutura de Entidades

{% if stack == "python-fastapi" %}
### Exemplo: Entidade Base (SQLModel)

```python
# src/domain/entities/base.py
from sqlmodel import SQLModel, Field
from datetime import datetime
from typing import Optional
import uuid

class BaseEntity(SQLModel):
 """Base entity with common fields"""
 id: uuid.UUID = Field(default_factory=uuid.uuid4, primary_key=True)
 created_at: datetime = Field(default_factory=datetime.utcnow)
 updated_at: datetime = Field(default_factory=datetime.utcnow)
 is_active: bool = Field(default=True)
 
 # LGPD: Campos PII devem ser marcados
 _pii_fields: list[str] = []
```

### Exemplo: Entidade de Domínio

```python
# src/domain/entities/user.py
from sqlmodel import SQLModel, Field
from pydantic import EmailStr
from .base import BaseEntity

class User(BaseEntity, table=True):
 """User entity"""
 email: EmailStr = Field(unique=True, index=True)
 full_name: str
 password_hash: str = Field(exclude=True) # Nunca expor
 phone: Optional[str] = None
 
 # LGPD: Campos PII
 _pii_fields = ["email", "full_name", "phone"]
```

### Migrações (Alembic)

```bash
# Criar migração
alembic revision --autogenerate -m "Create user table"

# Aplicar migração
alembic upgrade head

# Validar esquema
alembic check
```

{% elif stack == "node-react" %}
### Exemplo: Schema Prisma

```prisma
// prisma/schema.prisma
model User {
 id String @id @default(uuid())
 email String @unique
 fullName String @map("full_name")
 passwordHash String @map("password_hash")
 phone String?
 createdAt DateTime @default(now()) @map("created_at")
 updatedAt DateTime @updatedAt @map("updated_at")
 isActive Boolean @default(true) @map("is_active")
 
 @@map("users")
 @@index([email])
}
```

### Migrações

```bash
# Criar migração
npx prisma migrate dev --name create_user_table

# Validar esquema
npx prisma validate
```

{% endif %}

